news.title: Vibhor Steel Tubes surges 193% in debut trade
news.para: The stock made its debut at Rs 421, reflecting gains of 178.81 per cent from the issue price on the BSE. The stock settled at Rs 442, up by 192.72 per cent over the IPO price.

news.title: Sweden's Oscar Properties says CEO and CFO resign
news.para: Oscar Properties, one of several highly indebted Swedish real estate groups buckling under soaring borrowing costs and slower demand, said in a statement Carl Janglin would stay on as CEO until a successor had been appointed.

news.title: Delhi: Signature View Apartments RWA asks DDA for payment of rent to residents willing to evacuate
news.para: ​According to the letter dated February 15, it has been almost 15 months since the IIT-Delhi report recommended immediate evacuation and dismantling of the towers in the housing society to save lives of allottees/residents.

news.title: Germany: Adler Group's chairman resigns
news.para: Following an extraordinary meeting of the board of directors, the major German landlord said Stefan Brendgen would replace Kirsten with immediate effect.

news.title: China cuts mortgage reference rate more than expected to revive property market
news.para: The five-year loan prime rate (LPR) was lowered by 25 basis points to 3.95% from 4.20% previously, while the one-year LPR was left unchanged at 3.45%.

news.title: Greater Noida: Industrial plot allotment scheme extended till February 27
news.para: The Industrial Scheme was floated by the Greater Noida Industrial Development Authority (GNIDA) with a registration closing date of February 19.

news.title: Jaipur: JDA to utilise land pooling act to acquire 164 hectares for Shivdaspura township
news.para: JDA officials stated that although the Act was framed in 2016, neither the earlier BJP government nor the previous Congress government used this Act.

news.title: Goa: Stone crushing units told to install CCTVs, no ops without GSPCB nod
news.para: Any new crushers should be allowed to operate only in dedicated crusher zones according to the sitting policies of GSPCB, the guidelines state.

news.title: Gujarat government to install 10 lakh solar panels under PM scheme
news.para: Solar Rooftop Scheme Surya-Gujarat Scheme was launched by the state govt from Aug 5, 2019, for the purpose of providing relief in electricity bills to residential consumers in the state and boost green energy generation.

news.title: Visakhapatnam development body to auction bulk land parcels, vacant plots
news.para: These VMRDA auctions will not only gauge the current market sentiment but also potentially influence real estate prices in neighbouring areas.

news.title: Tamil Nadu finance minister launches new concrete housing scheme for rural poor
news.para: Presenting the Budget, the minister said the new scheme named ‘Kalaignarin Kanavu Illam’ would be implemented with the objective of constructing eight lakh concrete houses in rural areas.

news.title: Bhopal: 280 families in Bhadbhada basti told to vacate houses in two days
news.para: Earlier in the day, a foot march in the colony was carried out and administration officials interacted with the residents and advised them to remove their encroachments

news.title: Bengaluru civic body can't insist on payment of 50% tax differential upfront: HC
news.para: Justice S Sunil Dutt Yadav made this observation in his interim order wherein several property tax demand notices issued against Gopalan Enterprises were stayed last Friday.

news.title: Akrama-Sakrama case may get rejected in SC: Karnataka minister
news.para: Responding to a query from Udupi MLA Yashpal Suvarana regarding the extension of deadlines for property regularization applications in rural areas under sections 94C and 94CC, Byregowda highlighted a significant issue faced by the govt.

news.title: Common services in housing society can't attract commercial power tariff: Court
news.para: The court of additional sessions judge Jasbir Singh, in its order dated Feb 17, directed the discom to refund Rs 70 lakh that was paid by Valley View Estate society along with interest at the rate of 6% per annum.

news.title: TCS leases four lakh sq ft office space in Noida
news.para: Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) leases 400,000 sq ft office space in Noida due to renewed demand. Delhi-NCR records highest leasing volume, with flex space sector leading. Supply increases, raising vacancy rate. Large corporations drive demand. Cushman & Wakefield comments. IT-BPM sector records high volume.

news.title: Byju's vacates four lakh sq ft office space in Bengaluru to cut costs
news.para: Byju's was paying a rental of about Rs 4 crore per month for the office space and had signed the rental agreement about 3.5 years ago with the Prestige Group.

news.title: Godrej Properties poised to exceed FY24's Rs 15,000-crore project addition guidance: Chairman
news.para: Godrej Properties expects to surpass its business development guidance, driven by a robust deal pipeline and ongoing consolidation. The recent acquisitions in the Hyderabad property market and Bengaluru hold significant revenue potential. The company anticipates delivering its best-ever annual performance.

news.title: SD Corporation extends bond payment by two months
news.para: The company has scheduled a coupon payment on 5.5% unlisted senior secured bonds of ₹750 crore due on January 31, 2024. Under the revised terms, the bondholders have agreed to reschedule the coupon payment to March 31 at 12% which will be payable half-yearly, the people cited above said.

news.title: Conversion from collector land fetches Maharashta Rs 640 crore in last five years
news.para: Salil Rameshchandra, president, Federation of Grantees of Government Land, said individual plot owners availed of the concessional scheme introduced by the state government in 2019.
